Chavez, blasting weak dollar, wants euro-denominated crude

http://www.dominicantoday.com/ap...e.aspx?
id=14102

Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez, an "anti-imperialist" antagonist of the United States, suggested as host of the OPEC ministerial meeting here Thursday that the cartel forsake the weak dollar and switch to the euro for pricing crude.

"The dollar is weakening, due above all to the irresponsibility of the government of the United States," he said in his speech opening the conclave of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries.

Chavez blamed the greenback's slide on the U.S. budget deficit - "the biggest in history" - and on what he called "an artificial economy, a veritable bubble on the point of bursting, that threatens the world."

He predicted the "end of the dictatorship of the dollar, currency of an empire that will fall in this century." Venezuela is already studying the idea of selling its oil in euros, Chavez said, while adding that he hopes to see the advent of a Latin American single currency analogous to the euro.
